15/02/2006
ZAGREB, Croatia -- President Stipe Mesic announced on Tuesday (14 February) that he plans a trip to Afghanistan within the next six months. During a visit to the Zagreb military barracks, where the seventh Croatian contingent is preparing for deployment to Kabul, Mesic noted that Afghan counterpart Hamid Karzai has always praised the performance of Croatian soldiers serving in the International Security Assistance Force there. (Novi list - 15/02/06; HINA - 14/02/06)
